  <h2>This block is a Phase 1-stub for Unit 5</h2>
  <p class="sub">Full content lands when Unit 5 is built out.</p>
  <p>Block 1 opens the unit by building a quantitative picture of the water cycle — not just "evaporation, condensation, precipitation," but reservoirs (ocean, ice, groundwater, atmosphere) with their <strong>sizes</strong> and <strong>residence times</strong>. Atmospheric water turns over in days; deep groundwater in millennia. Today also names the stakeholders in the Cauvery dispute as the unit's anchor case — water is a <em>political</em> resource, and the cycle is where the politics gets grounded.</p>
